# Import Statement

To use classes from another package:

```java
import packageName.ClassName;
```

Example:

```java
import student.Student;
```

---

# What Does Import Mean?

Import tells Java:

```text
Use this class
from another package
```

---

# Example

```java
import java.util.Scanner;
```

Scanner belongs to:

```text
java.util package
```

---

# Using Built-in Packages

Example:

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc =
                new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.print(
                "Enter Name: ");

        String name =
                sc.nextLine();

        System.out.println(
                name);
    }
}
```

---

# Output

```text
Enter Name: Sanjay

Sanjay
```

---

# Importing Multiple Classes

```java
import java.util.Scanner;
import java.util.ArrayList;
```

---

# Wildcard Import

Instead of importing classes one by one:

```java
import java.util.*;
```

This imports:

```text
Scanner
ArrayList
HashMap
LinkedList
etc.
```

---

# Example

```java
import java.util.*;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        ArrayList<String> names =
                new ArrayList<>();

        names.add("Sanjay");

        System.out.println(
                names);
    }
}
```

---

# Output

```text
[Sanjay]
```

---

# Fully Qualified Name

Instead of import:

```java
import java.util.Scanner;
```

You can write:

```java
java.util.Scanner sc =
        new java.util.Scanner(System.in);
```

This is called:

```text
Fully Qualified Name
```

---

# Example

```java
public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        java.util.Scanner sc =
                new java.util.Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.println(
                "Hello");
    }
}
```

---

# Name Conflict Problem

Suppose:

```text
student.Student

teacher.Student
```

Both have same class name.

---

Without packages:

```text
Conflict
```

---

With packages:

```java
student.Student
```

```java
teacher.Student
```

No conflict.

---

# Example

Package 1:

```java
package student;

public class Student {

}
```

Package 2:

```java
package teacher;

public class Student {

}
```

Both are valid.

