# Key Takeaways

- Packages organize Java classes.
- Packages prevent naming conflicts.
- Built-in packages are provided by Java.
- User-defined packages are created by programmers.
- Import allows access to package classes.
- Packages should always use lowercase names.
- Large Java projects rely heavily on package structures.

---

# Conclusion

Packages are one of the most important organizational tools in Java. They help group related classes, prevent naming conflicts, improve code readability, and make large projects easier to manage. Understanding packages is essential for building professional Java applications and enterprise software.
